title: Bug 109350 - Output parameter should display in data set dialog
OB: The output parameter does not display in the data set dialog when the stored procedure is called from an Oracle database. As a result, there is no data returned in the query result page.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog. This will ensure that the data returned from the stored procedure is visible in the query result page.
SR: To reproduce the issue: 1. Call the stored procedure from an Oracle database. 2. Check the query result page for data. 3. Note that the output parameter is not displayed in the data set dialog. Expected result: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
